                                    <watches>0</watches>
                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14152112" author="mreutegg" created="Mon, 29 Sep 2014 19:19:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Added a test (currently ignored) in &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/r1628262&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/r1628262&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14153013" author="mreutegg" created="Tue, 30 Sep 2014 09:34:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The root cause for this issue is the snapshot isolation (SI) implemented by DocumentNodeStore. SI does not guarantee serializability of schedules. The write skew anomaly occurs because adding a node in Oak usually does not modify the parent. A conflict goes undetected if the parent is concurrently removed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14153187" author="mreutegg" created="Tue, 30 Sep 2014 14:11:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Improved test and changed the commit logic to always set the _children field on the parent of an added node, even if it is already present. This materializes the conflict and result in a merge failure for one of the commits. Done in &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/r1628447&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/r1628447&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14154431" author="mreutegg" created="Wed, 1 Oct 2014 06:25:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Test is now enabled. &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/r1628608&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/r1628608&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14154493" author="mreutegg" created="Wed, 1 Oct 2014 07:14:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Merged into 1.0 branch in &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/r1628625&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/r1628625&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14169107" author="mreutegg" created="Mon, 13 Oct 2014 09:20:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bulk close for Oak 1.0.7&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
